        "id": "3110AD03E6B01D6A4FC724F58CA3EA1D",
        "headline": "Liquid Carton Packaging Market Forecast Points Higher Toward 2035, Driven by Sustainability Push",
        "timestamp": "2026-04-16T02:45:54",
        "source": {
          "id": "665423",
          "name": "IndexBox",
          "rank": "RANK_3"
        },
        "url": "https://www.indexbox.io/blog/liquid-carton-packaging-market-forecast-points-higher-toward-2035-driven-by-sustainability-push/",
        "chunks": [
          {
            "cnum": 7,
            "text": "Major trends: Explosive growth of oat milk requiring specific lipid and oxygen barriers, Entry of major dairy companies into plant-based, leveraging existing carton supply chains, Demand for clean-label, preservative-free products pushing barrier technology limits, Expansion into adjacent categories like plant-based yogurts and creamers in cartons, and Strong co-branding opportunities linking carton sustainability to product ethos.\nRepresentative participants: Oatly, Danone (Alpro), Califia Farms, SunOpta, Blue Diamond Growers, and Vitasoy.\nLiquid Foods (Soups, Sauces, Wine) (estimated share: 12%)\nThis segment encompasses a diverse range of products where cartons provide an alternative to cans, glass jars, and flexible pouches. Current applications include ambient soups, cooking sauces, passata, and increasingly, wine in bag-in-box formats. The demand mechanism is one of substitution and new category creation. Through 2035, growth will be driven by cartons' advantages: lighter weight than glass, better shelf appeal than cans, and superior barrier vs. simple pouches. For wine, the growth driver is the expansion of casual consumption and sustainability-conscious younger consumers adopting bag-in-box. For cooking sauces, it's convenience and portion control. Key indicators are the adoption rate of cartons by major food brands for shelf-stable cooking aids, the growth rate of the premium bag-in-box wine segment, and development of easy-open, recloseable features for liquid foods. Current trend: Niche but high-value segment with innovation potential.",
